  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_ref11_j69" level="series"><did><unittitle>Con-Agra Shutdown Efforts</unittitle><unitid>I.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61435</unitid></did><scopecontent id="aspace_20ece86e56d0ebd05db54add26e95ea2"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Series I consists of material related to events preceding and surrounding the shutdown of the plant and the formation of the organization. There is a minimal amount of information about Greyhound, the company that sold the Armour plant to Con-Agra. It contains correspondence with Con-Agra about the possible re-opening of the plant and re-hiring of the former employees. There is some information about plant-closing benefit packages from Armour, and biographical information and photocopied pictures of the board of directors of Con-Agra. It contains proposals from Con-Agra concerning labor agreements, but many things are not dated, making the sequence of events difficult to determine.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref12_f4e" level="file"><did><unittitle>Con-Agra Letters</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61436</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">1/5/83 to 7/17/84</unitdate><container id="aspace_97131de7295cd5dfb076a26b748bbb2e" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_fee0700a0e558fa67bd2acdcc938f0ae" parent="aspace_97131de7295cd5dfb076a26b748bbb2e" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref13_opa" level="file"><did><unittitle>Final Agreement Proposal from Con-Agra</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61437</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation">11/28/83</unitdate><container id="aspace_f9393b37143c70e1e5d2475c00942474" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d4c6b3ce44de4bac451c375e63269bef" parent="aspace_f9393b37143c70e1e5d2475c00942474" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref14_s1h" level="file"><did><unittitle>Board of Directors, Con-Agra</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61438</unitid><container id="aspace_e184c2c5f592f7d91fb6f4d36df8f31a" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_8f27579b130cd9cc04eb38045a2536bc" parent="aspace_e184c2c5f592f7d91fb6f4d36df8f31a" type="folder">3</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref15_h24" level="file"><did><unittitle>Old Proposed Agreement Contract</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61439</unitid><container id="aspace_39ec4cc18d35fc9b4249f44f25761ca4" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c6ede7435ec106e4b9ff15f16f8bfa0d" parent="aspace_39ec4cc18d35fc9b4249f44f25761ca4" type="folder">4</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref16_jbs" level="file"><did><unittitle>Armour's Retiree Medical Benefits</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61440</unitid><container id="aspace_8a8911ce803aaa8b45877581085a9ab2" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_0ac5311c4b96f6a99dcdd07972e2e8e8" parent="aspace_8a8911ce803aaa8b45877581085a9ab2" type="folder">5</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref17_bl4" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters from AWU to Leaders</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61441</unitid><container id="aspace_45abc4b157a5d01428d6a232ae11fcd8" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_6fdd19a8036d1bab169e5fdbbfb2ae73" parent="aspace_45abc4b157a5d01428d6a232ae11fcd8" type="folder">6</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref18_13r" level="file"><did><unittitle>I.D.A. Con-Agra Loan</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61442</unitid><container id="aspace_ecff92e2f2d15ba8d25d879c23eb4962" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_210e95b21af542fc1535146ff3283f7f" parent="aspace_ecff92e2f2d15ba8d25d879c23eb4962" type="folder">7</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref19_98j" level="file"><did><unittitle>Master Agreement-Presentation, Re-Opening, Summary</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61443</unitid><container id="aspace_26ae4b78a5eb608af20e138f8323c311" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_ead9d5adaa64fb8193d6aca92f484b87" parent="aspace_26ae4b78a5eb608af20e138f8323c311" type="folder">8</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref20_2er" level="file"><did><unittitle>Armour Co. Medical or Master Agreement</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61444</unitid><container id="aspace_192aea1cc3f3891131109dcc8ffbd304" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_7f83057091f233cf53890fd445450bb0" parent="aspace_192aea1cc3f3891131109dcc8ffbd304" type="folder">9</container></did></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_ref22_w22" level="series"><did><unittitle>AWU Organized Labor Efforts</unittitle><unitid>II.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61445</unitid></did><scopecontent id="aspace_764862bb3d3dcc504573915295ab7ea0"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Series II concerns AWU and their efforts to organize. There are also two sub-series related to particular activities. The first has to do with their efforts to start up their own business as an Employee Stock Ownership Plan, and the second pertains to the boycott of Armour and its subsidiary's products. AWU's activities were not documented in any consistent way, and there are wide gaps in the information. There are meeting agendas, hand-written notes, hand-written member lists, mailing labels, typed mailing lists, newspaper clippings (often without dates), minimal financial information, articles of incorporation, and flyers.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref75_fpz" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Administrative Material</unittitle><unitid>1.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61446</unitid></did><scopecontent id="aspace_bffa879cceb5dcf02ceff4e46f9bb8f6"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Sub-Series 1 is a collection of administrative material consisting of old letters to AWU, financial reports, letters from leaders, as well as rejections to propodals.</p></scopecontent><c03 id="aspace_ref23_35q" level="file"><did><unittitle>Old Letters, AWU</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61447</unitid><container id="aspace_73d50f7cbeb6d476c1bf73dccc140a63" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c8ffada47fc9fdc93bfed9ef8e523450" parent="aspace_73d50f7cbeb6d476c1bf73dccc140a63" type="folder">10</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref24_km5" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mailing Addresses, AWU</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61448</unitid><container id="aspace_90799dcf0e56056e978a9c7727d2ac4e" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e0035df46991e1af09788e73a13b77b2" parent="aspace_90799dcf0e56056e978a9c7727d2ac4e" type="folder">11</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref25_dvw" level="file"><did><unittitle>AWU Financial Report</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61449</unitid><container id="aspace_50587a398d535d26bbb748c7e6398692" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_13f803bcbbba04cd488a78e74dd04ffb" parent="aspace_50587a398d535d26bbb748c7e6398692" type="folder">12</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref26_t01" level="file"><did><unittitle>PPP and AWU Fight Song</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61450</unitid><container id="aspace_5b52c80cadc99a28a13c2639a00caa0e" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1ae7ad63765926de6a43f044706f7666" parent="aspace_5b52c80cadc99a28a13c2639a00caa0e" type="folder">13</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref27_2tq" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters to Leaders, 1/84</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61451</unitid><container id="aspace_f4b80bce616971b105b3d6a423e49452" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_f8357445a28415e55dca00fcdf962b22" parent="aspace_f4b80bce616971b105b3d6a423e49452" type="folder">14</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref28_z3p" level="file"><did><unittitle>Address Sheets AWU</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61452</unitid><container id="aspace_9fae645beb602121cd1dc024e403900d" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a2db9949bdd33a9379a45c381294664f" parent="aspace_9fae645beb602121cd1dc024e403900d" type="folder">15</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref29_cgh" level="file"><did><unittitle>Rejected 8 Proposal</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61453</unitid><container id="aspace_bad5e899d6fe88ba4e18607c914530ad" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_362b2066eb8da5903b20a28f19bf1f94" parent="aspace_bad5e899d6fe88ba4e18607c914530ad" type="folder">16</container></did></c03></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref30_l0i" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Efforts to Purchase Plant</unittitle><unitid>2.</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61454</unitid></did><scopecontent id="aspace_a626bb0d7620ff0eedadf860b372787d"><head>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Sub-Series 2 pertains to the group's attempts to purchase a facility and start their own business. It reflects the involvement of the Center for Entrepreneurial Development in having a feasibility study done. AWU received a $5000 grant from the Pittsburgh National Bank Foundation for that project. Professor Dwight Baumann of Carnegie-Mellon University and a class of mechanical engineering students undertook the preliminary study. Part of this was the development of a proposal to the Ben Franklin Partnership for an engineering study of the "state of the art" in meat processing. An application was also made to the Commonwealth Employee Ownership Assistance Program, and the city and county each pledged $25,000 in matching funds to supplement the state funds. Then state Rep. Tom Murphy, D-North Side, vocally supported the cause of AWU, and was part of a steering committee for Pittsburgh Provision and Packing. The steering committee requested bids for the role of project coordinator for the feasibility study, and Philadelphia Association for Cooperative Enterprise (PACE) was chosen. All of this activity is documented to some extent in this sub-series, through correspondence and various reports, and photocopies of proposals and applications.</p></scopecontent><c03 id="aspace_ref31_cky" level="file"><did><unittitle>Production Armour Plant</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61455</unitid><container id="aspace_9b3f5b8e18d63e199d07e7464364caea" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b0fb22bb5349706fc5282e405265e923" parent="aspace_9b3f5b8e18d63e199d07e7464364caea" type="folder">17</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref32_nro" level="file"><did><unittitle>Plants to Look At</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61456</unitid><container id="aspace_8d37507e7ac9e606dd9d206eead1c03b" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1d234b953ae9a835ee33509fe64788fd" parent="aspace_8d37507e7ac9e606dd9d206eead1c03b" type="folder">18</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_ref33_c8n" level="file"><did><unittitle>Leaders City, County, State</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/61457</unitid><container id="aspace_0f630e5b264c6388ebfc12e5f75f8c86" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_0763d54a2c7a2b20a81eed8ba6c3c155" parent="aspace_0f630e5b264c6388ebfc12e5f75f8c86" type="folde